name: Jason Cooper
review_text: The pizza and wings were delicious. They delivered my food in a timely manner. I would highly recommend this restaurant!

name: Jules Nativio
review_text: I have been waiting to leave this review until after the lockdown was lifted as I did not want to affect any business for them. I ordered Zeeks lot from the Chandler ( warner) location.  However, the last time I ordered in March, a liter of Pespi was delivered instead if Diet Pepsi.  Not a big deal and driver told me he would adjust my bill. No problem. Two days later, I called up Zeeks as the adjustment never occured.  Whoever I spoke to acted as if I did something wrong. He had an attitude and was rude. He said he could not adjust the bill (credit to my debit card) the day after a transaction. I've never heard of this lack of fucntionality. He told me he could not add a credit to my account.  He told me he could not note my account for future orders. Instead, he could mail me a gift card.  I asked if I could pick it up.  He said it has to be mailed.  Weird but okay.  Well I never received the gift card and have not ordered Zeeks since. I was ordering from then once a week, so their loss.  Good pizza though and owner seems very cool. Actually came out on a delivery once.

name: Nelson Slater
review_text: It was my first time here, and they got a new returning customer! The food was tasty, and the customer service was excellent. Food was cooked and seasoned just to perfection. It is our new pizza place without any hesitation.

name: David Goodman
review_text: Love their pizza.

name: Jenna G
review_text: Zesty Zzeeks is what's up! Ordered last night for the first time and was pleasantly surprised! Delivery was fast and contact-less, and pizza was hot! It was delicious, even the gluten free, and that's always a gamble. We found our new pizza spot!

name: Mark Jordan
review_text: Great pizza and wings!! Love them!!

name: Hunter Huisken
review_text: I have ordered food from two locations over the past couple years, and this establishment without a doubt, is best service in pizza

name: Dean Doherty
review_text: Pretty typical of what passes for pizza in the Phx metro.  Unremarkable Dominoes-like sauce, original crust ok, average amount of toppings, no real distinctive flavor.  A pizza.  And an average one at best.  One level above Dominoes/PJohns.  Poor value imo given price.

name: Leehawk NewMoon
review_text: New York style pizza was overcooked almost no cheese fr

name: Chance Houston
review_text: Avoid! Does not enforce posted mask policy. Did not clean counter surfaces after mask-less customer used card reader. It’s a free country, get your pizza somewhere else.

name: Aaron Simmons
review_text: Wings were just ok tonight. Pizza you can tell has been sitting in the heating area it was rock hard. Also, dont ask for tip over the phone before the product is delivered. It is unfortunate because it's so close to the house. It feels like they have been getting worse, they used to be awesome. We had a similar problem a few months ago. The manager was very apologetic and was supposed to send some coupons which never showed up. We dont want anything free just want it to be correct so not looking for anything. We dont usually review online because we know the reputational damage it can cause but, in this case and past performance it was warranted.

name: Mia Perkins
review_text: The pizza here is amazing. And the boneless wings....dont get me started . Juicy flavorful and you can just eat one! Amd why would you! They also have a few flavors of Eegees and coming from Tucson i have missed Eegees!

name: Niqui Kukel
review_text: Not the quality I was expecting for the price. Mediocre at best... Maybe the dine in experience paid better homage to their pricing? Sad to say even with .70 wing special we will not be going back.

name: Josh
review_text: Wings were pretty good. Only thing is I wish they were more crispy. Nice big juicy wings with plenty of ranch dipping sauce.

name: Kayla Koglmeier
review_text: My little one and I always come and get Eegee's and the staff are ALWAYS super polite, respectful, and friendly. We love coming here. Thank you guys for being awesome!

name: monika letzte
review_text: This is truly an amazing place for grub the staff are all kind and work hard on delivering high quality food for their costumers. I rate 5 stars the food is a wide variety and delicious

name: Antonio RIVERA
review_text: Love the pizza also the wings are great mango habanero is my favorite. And reasonably  priced. Plus they have beer!🤘

name: melissa scotty
review_text: Great staff. Great food

name: Paula Armenta
review_text: First time there and was very disappointed. Won't be going back.

name: Desiree Sherant
review_text: Pizza and wings are very good! Great customer service too. I messed up placing my online order (selected boneless when I wanted bone-in) they without fuss or anything made me a new order of wings the way I wanted it and gave me the messed up wings as well.

name: john hobbs
review_text: Good pizza but don't order the Chicken sub

name: Jayden E
review_text: I love their food but this is crazy. It’s very inconsistent. We order cauliflower wings all the time but most time we only get a few pieces now. Today was the worst yet ever. Paid 7.99 for just 9 small cauliflower. I cannot believe it. I won’t be ordering again.  Once we made two orders of them and one had 10 pieces and the other had about 15. I don’t understand.

name: Krista McKinney
review_text: The pizza and wings are amazing!   I have no picture because we ate it too fast.  Delivery was exactly when they said it would be.  The owners are very community minded and have been selling bread flour and yeast and other staples at their cost during the covid pandemic.  I appreciate their care for the community in keeping the dining rooms closed until it's safe to reopen.

name: Keshaundra
review_text: I was just here yesterday and my wings were so hard that I couldn’t bite into them. I ordered garlic Parmesan and couldn’t even taste the seasoning at all. Very disappointed in this because two days before I had wings and they were amazing.

name: Michelle Brungardt
review_text: We read about Zesty Zzeeks in the paper and had decided we wanted to try it, although we live in the West Valley.  We were amazed!  We ordered the Margherita and Grand Slam pizzas on St Louis Thin crust...I never knew pizza could taste that fresh and amazing.  The crust was perfect and each pizza had plenty of toppings.  This won't be our last visit!

name: Julie Shade
review_text: We’ve never eaten here yet… I just want to give you guys a shoutout… During the whole quarantine you guys sold supplies… That’s pretty stellar of what you did! Can’t wait to try you guys out someday soon.

name: Cory Chapman
review_text: I just got a good pizza.  From an extrovert. In the middle of a global pandemic. Guy shows up, ignores request to leave pie outside, is wearing a bandana, directly ignores me standing back and asking to leave pie on recycle bin, wants to have a five minute conversation about stray cats.

name: Jesse Heimann
review_text: Wings are the BEST! We love honey barbecue, but just discovered the place so working our way through the sauces! Pizza rocks too, but one of these times we're going to try some of their gluten free, keto pizzas.

name: Alex S
review_text: At 7:12 PM I called and placed an order for delivery and was told 45 minutes (documented call).At 8:35 PM  I called about the non-delivered order, and was told "the driver just left with that order (documented call).At 8:58 PM I called about the non-delivered order (documented call).  The employee said they couldn't find any record of any order.  After several iterations of going over location and phone numbers to verify details, the employee called me a liar and hung up on me.At 9:04 PM I called back to request the owners names, and the employee said he would hand up on me again (documented call).  I obtained the owner's names.At 9:12 my phone rings - It's Zeek's, a manager, telling me "they checked their phone system and found all my calls, but lost my order."   You don't say?During a time when restaurants should be doing everything, this employee(s) is losing orders, lying about orders being en route, in turn calling customers liars, and, saving the best for last - threatening finishing off the interaction by hanging up on them.   Oh, and then threatening to do it all again.-- Insane ---My recommendation is immediate drug testing for all employees.  I suspect this would result in the necessary final outcome of a (mostly) new staff.  Thankfully the evening manager was sane and polite.

name: Tristan Labadie
review_text: I'm not sure when you decided to make your thin crust a domino's wannabe. That was the most disappointing thing I have ever seen when I opened the pizza box up.

name: Isaac Nib
review_text: Bad deals and they steal others recipe

name: Mark H
review_text: The best

name: Jordan Webb
review_text: Horrible place

name: Jason SCANLON
review_text: The owners are awesome. Thank you for all you do for the community! They have offered supplies to the general public in a time of need. There were so many people behaving badly while  you were doing a good deed, it makes me lose faith in humanity. Thank you for kindness and generosity and for putting up with the few bad apples for the chance to help the the rest of us.

name: mitch kassel
review_text: Their gf boneless wings are really good. May be the only spot I know that offers them

name: Tandy Giefer
review_text: Took my elderly parents and two dogs to pick up a margarita pizza and bag of zeppollis  last night at ZZeeks pizza in Chandler, first time trying the place.  We opened my hatchback and had a picnic in almost empty parking lot.  Both were a 10!  Thank you for being open, and will order again.  Looking forward to being on that patio.  Hope you are dog friendly!!  Delicious!  Remember to tip these hardworking people, no matter what!!’

name: Brent Simonson
review_text: This is LITERALLY the 6th or 7th time I've had to send a salad back AFTER I ORDERED IT WITH NOOOOOOO OLIVES!!! They pre-make salads and "take out" the ingredient you ask them too. Zero attention to detail with EVERY SALAD I've ordered. If you have allergies to an ingredient, make your own salad. The pizza is FANTASTIC as usual, just please pay attention to your customers and their needs.

name: Charlie Cabot
review_text: Great pizza and wings

name: Natalie Seder
review_text: Good place for a cheap, quick and tasty lunch! Best bread sticks!!!! If you don't believe me, try them for yourself.

name: T Gilmore
review_text: Man this is good pizza!!  I love the different options for crust, everything has so much flavor and its not very greasy.  The service was really good and the owners are so friendly.  Great place!

name: Melinda Roberts
review_text: Great tasting pizzas.

name: Barry Graziano
review_text: Employees were pleasant. We ordered chicken Philly cheese steak, fried zuchinni, 10 pice regular bone in wings, and fries. They bought us a chicken parm. Apologetic and left the chicken parm for us and made the chicken philly. We came here for the wings, heard they were great. Disappointing...very very small, smallest wings I have every seen,  and appeared over cooked. Tasted okay..underwhelming, not worth price. The pizza looked really good, I should have ordered that instead. I really liked the crust options offered, cauliflower and gluten free. Kudos for this, I wish I had tried them instead of the wings. I would go back and try the pizza.

name: james davidson
review_text: The low carb keto options are delicious ! The have an amazing broccoli cheddar crust!

name: Megan Van Damme
review_text: We saw this when driving by one day and we are a family of hardcore pizza eaters so naturally wanted to try it out. I ordered online and had it delivered. We loved the sound of a lot of pizzas but got two specialty pizzas in one. We also ordered a small pizza for our kids that have a flavor profile that only accepts cheese. This pizza was absolutely outstanding! I cannot wait to order more and work my way through the menu. I will HAPPILY order from them again. Delivery was prompt, pizza was fresh (and delicious), and the prices were reasonable. Seriously, if you haven't had it, definitely give it a try! I can't wait to try the wings! Consider us future repeat customers :)

name: Karen Peterson
review_text: Great food and very nice workers

name: Moriah Morgan
review_text: On Sundays this place has a SUPER great sale on wings. Which, by the way, their wings are TO DIE FOR. I also came here while pregnant to pick up food for everyone, and one of the workers helped me carry all of it out to my car. They were so sweet and made sure I got inside the car safely and everything. Also, my absolute favorite pizza from here is the margherita pizza. Oh. My. God. DELICIOUS. We go as often as we can and plan to go there soon. Must try!

name: steve
review_text: Excellent pizza and appetizers, and always well staffed so the wait times are usually minimal. Super friendly and clean pizza spot!

name: Mike Myers
review_text: Best Family owned Pizzeria in the Valley! I've been a customer at Awatukee  for years Best lunch special around.   Now that Chandler is open on Arizona Ave by my house, my family is a huge fan as well.  BBQ chicken pizza yum ! Love the Pepperoni  that cups up old school style #BestPizza

name: Serena Pruett
review_text: Love this place! Always fast and friendly service. Anytime you are there waiting every single  employee that sees you will ask if you've been helped or need anything while you are waiting. Zzeeks has made me a big fan of cauliflower crust, I just might like it better than traditional crust, the crunch and flavor are amazing.

name: A Ski
review_text: Great fast delivery. Yummy food.

name: Anthony Shepherd
review_text: Great people great food!

name: Doug Louton
review_text: Doesn't matter if I eat in or get my food delivered, everything is always just as ordered, happy friendly staff.

name: Laurie McGill
review_text: Had a delicious salad and really loved the quality and flavor of my slice.

name: Natalie Garner
review_text: Their pizza is good, but the customer service has gotten terrible. They totally got my order wrong and after I drove back and waited for them to remake it, it was wrong again and they offered me nothing for my trouble! When the manager brought out the third pizza I told him I had placed my order two hours earlier and asked for my money back even though they had finally gotten it right. He did and so I am changing my review from 1 star to 3, but please still work on your service!

name: Marilyn Danks
review_text: Huge fan of Zeeks in Ahwatukee and Tempe. Thought this location would have the same level of service and quality, but this was a disappointing experience. For being a Friday slower than I would expect Friday night, it was irritating that to dine in, it took over 45 minutes to get a pizza and gluten free wings. During that extend wait time, a customer came in with her previously picked up pizza and I overheard her saying that her daughter isn’t supposed to eat gluten, and the cauliflower crust pizza she had ordered came out as a normal dough pizza but she didn’t catch it until after her daughter had already eaten a piece. This is so horrible because my husband is celiac and their caution with food preparation is one of the reasons we love this chain. Whether it’s a lack of training or just carelessness on the part of the employees, it was not okay. Won’t be visiting this location again.

name: Devin Schnackenberg
review_text: We are frequent customers. Never had a bad experience or a bad pizza. If there were somewhere that could out Pizza the Hut.. this is it.

name: April Nye
review_text: We've tried the cauliflower pizza in the past and it was delicious! It is limited to a 10" however so that's a bummer. Tonight we tried out the 2x Dough and it did not disappoint. Have not eaten inside the restaurant, only had delivery. Both times were quick and pizza was exactly as ordered. Very impressed and will recommend to friends 👍

name: Brandi Rodriguez
review_text: Good pizza

name: Xavier Starr
review_text: Went in early today a bought a pizza only to take it home and found hairs! I have ate here on a couple occasion and I have never found hairs on top of that I wasn't helped as fast as I normally do and it wasn't even busy!! I used to love this place but I might reconsider eating somewhere else.

name: kim gaworski
review_text: Best wings ever , and prompt delivery! Most sauces are wayyyy to spicy for me but even without, best I’ve had hands down! Delivered pizza was not good, comparable to the one you can pick up for $5.00.

name: GamesDream
review_text: I walked in around 5-6 today and the place was over crowded and not a family environment!! RUDE STAFF!! Customer service was horrible if non existent! I tried to go in for a simple meal with the family and wasn't greeted so we left.. will not be coming back anytime soon!

name: AG'S Reviews
review_text: Extremely rude! My husband and I had ordered a day ago from here. We called because we wanted to try and give them another shot. My pizza bowl tasted off. Now this place is expensive as it is. So we wanted a refund or a replacement. A girl on the phone told my husband with an extremely bad attitude that no one could help us and wouldn't even hand the dang phone to a manager like we had requested. We called back an hour later and we finally got to talk to the manager. He was also extremely rude. He implyed we didn't actually buy anything when we would show proof of our repcipet but threw it away in THERE trash by the way. We have the charge on our bank account so don't try and play that bull that we didn't buy from here. He wasn't even budging to try and help. Definitely WILL NOT be coming back here ever again.

name: John S
review_text: Food was good. Reasonably priced.  The atmosphere was a little lacking. I figured since it was a dine in type of place they'd have at least some music playing in background. Overall not bad.

name: Ada Ayala
review_text: The wings order was wrong,I ordered hot and I didn't get them

name: Kimber Clark
review_text: Mac & cheese bites just ok. Didn't try anything else yet.

name: Mayvonne Stewart
review_text: Best wings, best calzones. Seriously good

name: Somer DeRose
review_text: We went yesterday for the first time to try out the .60 wings. I love wings and tolerate pizza, so I fully expected to eat only wings while my family ate pizza, but when it came out and I tried a bite, I was hooked and filled up on pizza instead. Don't get me wrong, the medium buffalo wings were great too (with good ranch and blue cheese), but the pizza surprised me. We found our new favorite pizza and wing place! 😋

name: Denice Colombero
review_text: The pizza was good and I had cauliflower crust. However, I walked in for a take out order, ordered a veggie pizza, got home and it was a margarita pizza. Kudos to them they did make it right.  Remade the pizza AND delivered it to my house.

name: Jimmy Reyes
review_text: I really liked the wings. The pizza also very good. The pricing was reasonable. The staff was very friendly.

name: Amanda Schultz
review_text: Keto pizza was soooooooooooo good! So glad I found this place while here for work.

name: Melanie Chryshelle
review_text: Best pizza in town!! 🤗

name: Samuel Dudding
review_text: Love zeeks good delivery thank you guys for hooking me up

name: Devin Shinn
review_text: Got the pizza and wings, great quality:portion:price ratio. Will definitely be back.

name: Tim Grijalva
review_text: Love Zesty Zzeeks!!! Their cauliflower pizza crust is the bomb!!! Quick,  orders always correct and super yummy! One of our "Go-to's!"
